        6/4/2015
    

It's tough to give any business a low review and sadly this review would have been much higher had it not been for the terrible front office staff. The nurse practitioner, Amanda Choi and Dr. Stewart are great. Both are personable and knowledgeable and I think Amanda is very through and has a great memory. However when it comes to the office, the buck stops here. Ann the front office person, is curt, rude and it feels like you're pulling teeth to get anything out of her. Her tone is always snide on the phone and you can tell that she is dispassionate about being in customer service. The office manager just hides behind Ann and there doesn't seem to be any gusto in this office due to the lack of leadership and disorganization by the front office. They claim to mail things to you address when nothing is received, they claim to call you for appointments - even going as far as to say that "I spoke to you" on x day, when that never happened and then they have fees for everything, even if you want a copy of your test results. The behavior of the office support staff has worsened over the years, which is why I have found another practice - that is just as knowledgeable as Dr. Stewart and Amanda, minus the rude front office team.




