Do you value your time?  Dr. Stewart's office won't.I've been to Dr. Stewart's office twice now (Oct 2014 & May 2015).  Both times I have gone for a routine visit, I have had to wait waaaaaaay too long.  This past visit (May 2015), I arrived at 8:30 for an 8:45 appointment.  I was perfectly fine to wait 15 minutes until my appointment.  I was the only one in the waiting room the entire time I was there.  At 8:45, I was called back to take my vitals, record my weight, and explain my symptoms.  After those quick checks, I was walked down the hall to an exam room and put in there by myself to wait to see someone.  And then...nothing.  An hour went by before I finally just got up and walked out.  I told the receptionist that I could no longer wait to see a physician based on my schedule.  I needed to see a physician but I didn't need for it to be an event requiring me to take a half-day off of work to see them.  After leaving, I fully expected one of James Stewart's staff to call me (perhaps apologetically) and attempt to reschedule.  Needless to say, they never called.  How's that for customer service?Find someone else.  I can assure you that your appointment time doesn't really matter to them.




