James L. Stewart | Professional Profile
 


























 









LinkedIn



















































Main content starts below.




James L. StewartVice President-Business Development, Technikon, LLC; Chairman, BioEnergy Producers AssociationLocationGreater Los Angeles AreaIndustryRenewables & EnvironmentCurrentTechnikon, LLCEducationUniversity of Southern California163 connectionsView James’ full profile. It's free!Your colleagues, classmates, and 500 million other professionals are on LinkedIn.View James’ Full ProfileSummaryMore than a decade ago, I learned of the potential for converting our nation’s organic waste streams into renewable fuels, biobased chemicals, electricity and other products, and the role these technologies could play in addressing critical issues like national security, energy independence, economic development and an improved environment. Soon thereafter, I put behind me a successful career in the entertainment industry to assist in bringing to reality the first commercial United States-based facility to produce biofuels and electricity from organic wastes.For these efforts and my other contributions to the industry, I have three times been recognized as one of the “Top 100 People in the Bio-Economy” in worldwide polls of the readers of Biofuels Digest.CAREER HIGHLIGHTSSustainable Earth Partners, LLC.  Currently a co-founding Principal, offering services in renewable energy consulting, technology commercialization and eco-industrial project development.  Stern Brothers & Co.Four years as a Strategic Consultant to the Alternative Energy practice of this industry-leading investment bank focusing on biobased technology project finance via the institutional bond markets.New Planet Energy, LLC/Bioengineering Resources, Inc.Seven-year association with the development and commercialization of a technology for the conversion of organic wastes to biofuels and renewable electricity, first with BRI, then with New Planet Energy.  Co-Founded New Planet Energy, LLC and served for three years as its Vice President – Marketing & Public Affairs.The Walt Disney CompanyThirteen years in marketing, corporate, governmental and investor relations at the Walt Disney Company--attaining the title of Vice President-Corporate Relations and Assistant to the President, overseeing the public affairs of one of the world’s best-known, high visibility corporate entities, while also serving for eleven years as Assistant to the Company’s President/Chief Operating Officer.ExperienceVice President Business DevelopmentTechnikon, LLCJuly 2015  –  Present (2 years 1 month)EducationUniversity of Southern CaliforniaB.A. Cinema-Television, M.B.A. FinanceB.A. Cinema-Television, M.B.A. FinanceSkillsMicrosoft ExcelMicrosoft WordPowerPointTeachingPublic SpeakingRenewable EnergyHow's this translation?Great•Has errorsThanks for your help!Honors & AwardsPrimary Community Involvement•	President, American Friends of the Edinburgh Festival. •	Member, Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences.•	Member, Board of Directors of the Los Angeles Chamber Orchestra for twenty years, serving on its Executive, Finance, Endowment, Marketing and Artistic Liaison Committees.  •	Founder and first Chairman of the Los Angeles Philharmonic Business & Professional Committee, which raises funds for the orchestra in the corporate community. View James’ full profile to...See who you know in commonGet introducedContact James directlyView James’ Full ProfileView this profile in another languageEnglishGermanPeople Also ViewedClark StilwellPresident at Land Investment Services, LLCThomas PoitierChief Financial Officer at Interdenominational Theological CenterDr. Al Sutton M.D., M.H.A.Student at WUSOMLawrence R. Garrison, Sr.CEO and President of LRG Associates LLC
